#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:75
msgid "cuda-oxide API sketch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:77
msgid ""
"cuda-oxide exposes WGMMA through low-level intrinsics that map directly to "
"the hardware instructions. A typical usage pattern:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:80
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::wgmma::{\n"
"    make_smem_desc, wgmma_fence, wgmma_commit_group, wgmma_wait_group,\n"
"    wgmma_mma_m64n64k16_f32_f16,\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"// After TMA has loaded A and B tiles into shared memory...\n"
"\n"
"// Build SMEM descriptors for the loaded tiles\n"
"let a_desc = unsafe { make_smem_desc(tile_a_ptr as *const u8) };\n"
"let b_desc = unsafe { make_smem_desc(tile_b_ptr as *const u8) };\n"
"\n"
"// Accumulator (4 warps × 8 floats per row = 64×64 tile)\n"
"let mut acc = [[0.0f32; 8]; 4];\n"
"\n"
"// Fence + issue WGMMA — all 128 threads in the warpgroup participate\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    wgmma_fence();\n"
"    wgmma_mma_m64n64k16_f32_f16(&mut acc, a_desc, b_desc);\n"
"    wgmma_commit_group();\n"
"    wgmma_wait_group::<0>(); // wait for all outstanding groups\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"// Accumulator in `acc` is now valid — store, transform, or pass to next "
"stage\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:107
msgid ""
"WGMMA is often paired with a **multi-stage pipeline**: while the tensor "
"cores process tile *k*, TMA loads tile *k+1* into a second shared memory "
"buffer. The barriers for TMA and MMA are separate, enabling full overlap of "
"data movement and computation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:115
msgid "tcgen05 — Blackwell (SM 100)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:117
msgid ""
"Blackwell introduces a fundamentally different matrix accelerator: "
"**tcgen05**. The key innovations are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:120
msgid ""
"**Single-thread issue.** Instead of a warpgroup-collective instruction, one "
"thread issues the MMA. The hardware distributes work internally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:122
msgid ""
"**Tensor Memory (TMEM).** A dedicated on-chip memory for accumulators, "
"separate from the register file. TMEM is larger and has different access "
"characteristics than registers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:125
msgid ""
"**Larger tiles.** tcgen05 supports shapes up to 256×256, vs WGMMA's 64×256."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:128
msgid "TMEM — Tensor Memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:130
msgid ""
"TMEM is a new tier in the memory hierarchy, sitting alongside the register "
"file but dedicated to matrix accumulation. It must be explicitly allocated "
"and deallocated:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:134
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::tcgen05::{TmemGuard, TmemUninit, TmemReady};\n"
"use cuda_device::SharedArray;\n"
"\n"
"static mut TMEM_ADDR: SharedArray<u32, 1> = SharedArray::UNINIT;\n"
"\n"
"// Allocate TMEM (warp-collective)\n"
"let tmem: TmemGuard<TmemReady, 128> = unsafe {\n"
"    TmemGuard::<TmemUninit, 128>::from_static(TMEM_ADDR.as_mut_ptr())\n"
"        .alloc()\n"
"};\n"
"\n"
"// ... use tmem for MMA ...\n"
"\n"
"// Deallocate (warp-collective, required before kernel exit)\n"
"unsafe { tmem.dealloc(); }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/matrix-multiply-accelerators.md:152
msgid ""
"`TmemGuard` uses typestates: `TmemUninit` → `alloc()` → `TmemReady` → "
"`dealloc()` → `TmemDeallocated`. The type system prevents using TMEM before "
"allocation or forgetting to deallocate — the latter would leak hardware "
"resources and fault."
msgstr ""

